  {
    "speaker": "interviewee",
    "tag": "ES",
    "text": "Yeah, my grandmother Brucha Laja Berman. And I think the blond one is Rivkala. And the dark-haired one is Hanala. And the other one, I think it's Bascia. I'm not sure. This is a picture of my father Zachary Zysman [? Zahariasz ?] in Lodz, Poland, taken before the war. He was wearing a nice fur coat because it must have been winter that time. This is a picture of my father [? Zahariasz ?] and my mother, [? Hanka, ?] and me, taken in Lodz before the war. I was kind of sad because I wanted something. And they didn't want to buy it for me, I guess. That's why the long face. This is a picture made in Sweden after the war. And it is my mother. It's my current husband Henry and me, made in Sweden after the war in Boras. This picture was made in Sweden on the day of my leaving Sweden for America. That's the fancy hat that I bought, so I look beautiful in the United States.",
